# pip-audit advisory allowlist — the E4 dependency CVE gate's documented escape hatch.
#
# Each non-comment, non-blank line is ONE OSV / PyPI advisory id (e.g. GHSA-xxxx-…
# or PYSEC-YYYY-…) to ignore, followed by a comment naming WHY it is accepted and
# WHEN to revisit. Keep this list SHORT and justified.
#
# This exists for the one case the gate cannot otherwise handle: an advisory that
# cannot be remediated WITHOUT breaking the determinism goldens — e.g. an `ortools`
# bump that changes the CP-SAT search path. Such a bump must go through a
# human-reviewed lock regen + golden re-pin, NEVER `pip-audit --fix`.
#
# format:  <ADVISORY-ID>    # reason / revisit-by
#
# (none currently — `pip-audit -r requirements.lock` reports the lock clean.)
